Rivers State Governor,  Nyesom Ezenwo Wike has given the chiefs and leaders of Andoni Local Government Area, a  72-hour ultimatum to ensure the immediate release of three kidnapped expatriates of Raffoul Nigeria Limited who are involved in the construction of the Unity Road in the area. Simeon Nwakaudu,Special Assistant to the Rivers State Governor on,  Electronic Media in a statement noted Wike had warned that failure to secure the release of the three expatriates kidnapped by Andoni youths at the expiration of the ultimatum; he would formally withdraw the recognition of all Government Recognised Chiefs in the local government area and cancel the Andoni aspect of the Unity Road project. The governor further stated that other communities across the state must take measures to protect contractors and workers executing projects for them. He said the same sanctions would be meted out to other communities where chiefs and leaders allow project contractors to be kidnapped by community youths.